# Orpal web shell — build-time environment (Vite). Copy to `.env.local` and fill in.

# ORPAL-016 / ORP-009 — wake-on-push (opt-in, off by default).
#
# The VAPID *public* key of the board's Web Push sender. It must match the
# keypair the relay board uses for ORP_PUSH_PROVIDER=webpush (ORP_VAPID_AUTH).
# Without it, the "Enable push notifications" toggle in Settings stays disabled
# (the browser can't create a usable Web Push subscription) and the device is
# only reachable while the app is open.
#
# Generate a VAPID keypair (e.g. `npx web-push generate-vapid-keys`); put the
# PUBLIC key here and the PRIVATE key on the board. urlsafe-base64, no quotes.
VITE_ORP_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=

# Native shells (Android FCM / iOS APNs) don't use this key: they register
# through the platform plugin instead and feed the resulting token to the same
# OrpalClient.setPushToken() path. Web Push is the only provider wired today.
